15. diribitae tabellae, ‘the votes were sorted.’ tabellae is not in the MSS. but is a conjecture of Wunder’s. The ordinary procedure at a Roman election is thus described :—The tribes were summoned one by one (vocatae) along the pontes into the saepta, or enelosures‚ booths. Each voter, being provided with a tablet (tabella), wrote the name of his candidate on it. The tablets were sorted (diribitae), the result announced (renuntiare) by a herald (praeco), and afterwards by the presiding magistrate.
